1.5 Justiο§¹cation
For many years and still, model rockets have used a parachute deployment system to slow down the vehicle after the apogee is reached. Thus, reducing impact energy and rocket damages when hitting the ground. It has proved to be a very optimal way to recover model rockets.
From this point of view, the project does not address an unsolved critical problem. It wants to recover a model rocket by landing it propulsively. The parachute approach has the same aim but the implementation is completely diο§Äerent. However, the use of a parachute cannot be stated as a landing since the more appropriate word would be βÄùa passively controlled descentβÄù.
The main justiο§¹cation for developing this project is to substitute a system that has been unchanged (and has ο§²aws) for many years with one that is more technologically advanced, reliable and allows rapid re-usability within minutes.
