3.2 Reference system
The six DoF system of equations (three axes: three force equations + three torque equations) must work with all the inputs in the same reference system. The body axis system (noninertial) is the one to hold the equations. All the forces must be expressed in these terms. The weight is translated from an inertial reference frame similar to the wide-known earth axis. The aerodynamic forces are translated from the wind reference frame (non-inertial). Finally, the thrust can be decomposed directly into the body axis of the rocket.
3.2.1 Direction Cosine Matrix (DCM)
