5.6.1 Pull Pin Switch
The Pull Pin Switch does exactly what its name means. Switch something when something is pulled. The system consists of a cable with two pins (signal and ground). The digital pin is put in a High state (4.8V). If the cable is connected closing the circuit, the ο§²ight computer detects that the signal is High. However, if the cable is disconnected, the circuit is opened and the computer will sense a Low signal (0V). Once the rocket is dropped, the wire will be pulled by an obstacle, and the ο§²ight computer will switch instantly between stand-by and Landing mode.

